{"format": "tiptap/v1", "updatedAt": "2026-06-22T08:47:10.539Z", "doc": {"type": "doc", "content": [{"type": "image", "attrs": {"src": "data:image/svg+xml;base64,", "alt": "Sequential/Functional API — concept overview"}}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "What Sequential & Functional APIs Are"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "In TensorFlow/Keras, "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Sequential API"}, {"type": "text", "text": " and "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Functional API"}, {"type": "text", "text": " are two high-level ways to build neural network models. They're part of the Keras API, which is TensorFlow's user-friendly interface for deep learning."}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Think of them as:\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Sequential API"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Stacking layers in a straight line (one input → layer 1 → layer 2 → output)\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Functional API"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Building arbitrary graphs where layers can connect in complex ways (multiple inputs/outputs, skip connections, shared layers)"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Both create the same underlying model, but Functional API offers full flexibility for complex architectures."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Why They Matter in Generative AI"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Different generative models need different architectures:"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Use Case"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "API"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Example Models"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Simple image generation"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Sequential"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Basic GANs, simple autoencoders"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Complex GANs (StyleGAN)"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Functional"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Multi-scale generators, skip connections"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Multi-modal generation"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Functional"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Text-to-image (CLIP + diffusion)"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Residual networks"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Functional"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Diffusion models with U-Net architecture"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Shared layers"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Functional"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Variational autoencoders with parameter sharing"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Multi-output models"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Functional"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "GANs with auxiliary classifiers"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Sequential is ideal for beginner-level problems, while Functional is \"industry strength\" for complex generative architectures."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Sequential API"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "What It Is"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "The "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Sequential model"}, {"type": "text", "text": " is the simplest way to create models in Keras—a linear stack of layers where each layer has exactly one input and one output."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "How to Build It"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "from tensorflow import keras\nfrom tensorflow.keras import layers\n\n# Method 1: Pass list of layers\nmodel = keras.Sequential([\n    layers.Input(shape=(784,)),        # Input layer [web:41]\n    layers.Dense(256, activation='relu'),  # Hidden layer [web:41]\n    layers.Dense(128, activation='relu'),\n    layers.Dense(784, activation='sigmoid')  # Output layer [web:41]\n])\n\n# Method 2: Add layers one by one\nmodel = keras.Sequential()\nmodel.add(layers.Input(shape=(784,)))\nmodel.add(layers.Dense(256, activation='relu'))\nmodel.add(layers.Dense(784, activation='sigmoid'))"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Complete Training Example"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "# Compile the model\nmodel.compile(\n    optimizer='adam',              # Optimizer [web:41]\n    loss='binary_crossentropy',    # Loss function [web:41]\n    metrics=['accuracy']           # Evaluation metrics [web:41]\n)\n\n# Train\nmodel.fit(\n    train_data,                    # Input tensors\n    train_labels,\n    epochs=100,\n    batch_size=32\n)\n\n# Evaluate\nmodel.evaluate(test_data, test_labels)\n\n# Predict\npredictions = model.predict(new_data)"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Key Characteristics"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Feature"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Description"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Single input/output"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "One input tensor, one output tensor"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Linear flow"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Layer N → Layer N+1 (no branching)"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Implicit connections"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Output of layer N is input to layer N+1 automatically"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Simple syntax"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Add layers with "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": ".add()"}, {"type": "text", "text": " or list"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Limited flexibility"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Can't create multi-input/output or skip connections"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "When to Use Sequential"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "✅ "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Best for"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":\n- Beginner-level image classification\n- Simple sentiment analysis\n- Basic regression tasks\n- Simple GANs with linear generator/discriminator\n- Data flows in "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "single path"}, {"type": "text", "text": " from input to output"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "❌ "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Not for"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":\n- Multiple inputs/outputs\n- Skip connections (ResNet)\n- Shared layers\n- Non-linear connections\n- Complex generative models (StyleGAN, U-Net)"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Functional API"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "What It Is"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "The "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Functional API"}, {"type": "text", "text": " is a powerful, flexible way to build complex neural networks where layers can have "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "multiple inputs/outputs, shared layers, or non-linear connections"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (branching, skip connections)."}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Unlike Sequential's linear stacking, Functional API treats layers as "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "functions"}, {"type": "text", "text": " that take tensors and return tensors, creating a "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "directed acyclic graph (DAG)"}, {"type": "text", "text": "."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "How to Build It"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "from tensorflow import keras\nfrom tensorflow.keras import layers\n\n# Step 1: Define input tensor\ninput_layer = keras.Input(shape=(784,))  # Input shape [web:41]\n\n# Step 2: Chain layers as function calls\nx = layers.Dense(256, activation='relu')(input_layer)  # Layer as function [web:41]\nx = layers.Dense(128, activation='relu')(x)\noutput = layers.Dense(784, activation='sigmoid')(x)\n\n# Step 3: Create Model from input/output tensors\nmodel = keras.Model(inputs=input_layer, outputs=output)  # [web:41]"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Key Features"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 4}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "1. Multiple Inputs"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "# Multi-input model (e.g., image + text for generation)\nimage_input = keras.Input(shape=(256, 256, 3))\ntext_input = keras.Input(shape=(100,))  # Text embedding\n\n# Process each input\nimage_features = layers.Conv2D(32, 3)(image_input)\ntext_features = layers.Dense(64)(text_input)\n\n# Combine\ncombined = layers.Concatenate()([image_features, text_features])\noutput = layers.Dense(10)(combined)\n\nmodel = keras.Model(inputs=[image_input, text_input], outputs=output)"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 4}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "2. Multiple Outputs"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "# Multi-output model (e.g., GAN with classifier)\ninput = keras.Input(shape=(784,))\nx = layers.Dense(256, activation='relu')(input)\n\n# Branch 1: Generate image\ngen_output = layers.Dense(784, activation='sigmoid')(x)\n\n# Branch 2: Classify\nclass_output = layers.Dense(10, activation='softmax')(x)\n\nmodel = keras.Model(\n    inputs=input,\n    outputs=[gen_output, class_output]  # Multiple outputs [web:41]\n)\n\n# Compile with multiple losses\nmodel.compile(\n    optimizer='adam',\n    loss=['binary_crossentropy', 'sparse_categorical_crossentropy'],\n    loss_weights=[0.8, 0.2]  # Weight losses [web:41]\n)"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 4}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "3. Skip Connections (ResNet)"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "# Residual block with skip connection\ninput = keras.Input(shape=(32, 32, 3))\n\nx = layers.Conv2D(32, 3, padding='same')(input)\nx = layers.ReLU()(x)\nx = layers.Conv2D(32, 3, padding='same')(x)\n\n# Skip connection: add input to output\nx = layers.Add()([x, input])  # Skip connection [web:41]\nx = layers.ReLU()(x)\n\noutput = layers.Conv2D(32, 3, padding='same')(x)\nmodel = keras.Model(inputs=input, outputs=output)"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 4}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "4. Shared Layers"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "# Shared embedding layer (e.g., for similar inputs)\nshared_embedding = layers.Embedding(input_dim=10000, output_dim=128)\n\ninput1 = keras.Input(shape=(100,), dtype='int32')\ninput2 = keras.Input(shape=(100,), dtype='int32')\n\n# Same layer used twice\nemb1 = shared_embedding(input1)\nemb2 = shared_embedding(input2)\n\n# Combine embeddings\ncombined = layers.Concatenate()([emb1, emb2])\noutput = layers.Dense(1)(combined)\n\nmodel = keras.Model(inputs=[input1, input2], outputs=output)"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "When to Use Functional API"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "✅ "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Best for"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (industry strength):\n- Multi-input models (e.g., CLIP, text-to-image)\n- Multi-output models (e.g., GANs with auxiliary classifiers)\n- Models with skip connections (ResNet, U-Net for diffusion)\n- Models with shared layers\n- Non-linear architectures with branching\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Complex generative models"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": StyleGAN, diffusion models, transformers"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Recommendation"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": For most people and most use cases, Functional API is what you should be using."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Sequential vs Functional Comparison"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Aspect"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Sequential API"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Functional API"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Flexibility"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Limited to linear stacks"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Arbitrary architectures"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Inputs"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Single input only"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Multiple inputs"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Outputs"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": 